<br>
and tamorfin you are wrong about that . i actually think that both simc and errtai could be outstanding guild leaders if they choose to be . they just have to step up and start taking full responsibility for the actions of there guild . if you recruit shitty people and get shit because of there actions and do nothing about it you reap what you sow . the hardest part of being a leader in any facet is looking at someone you like and having to discipline them because they fucked up , even fire someone if that is what needs to be done (yes i have had to do so on a few occasions ). when you participate in a public discussion defending that person and make accusations about the integrity of the people making the charges , imho you owe those people a public apology when you have been shown that you were mistaken . had they simply come and said we are aware of the accusations and are investigating it , anyone that has had encounters with wriath pls bring them to my attention at my email and then come back and said apparently the charges leveled against wriath were true and he has been removed from the guild for his actions and given a general apology to all involved this thread would not be 38 pages and counting . not to mention the side benefit of people saying to themselves hmm looks like rota is tired of having a bad rep due to shitbag players and is doing something about it . they would have gotten some respect for there actions instead of losing respect like they have .<br>
<br>
rota has a lot of outstanding players and i have friends that wear the rota tag . this isnt a tso vs rota thing at all . this is about being a leader . if one of my main engines throws a rod through the side of the block and ruins a 2 million dollar engine block i dont run down and start pointing fingers . i start an investigation to find out what caused the problem , why the incident happend , could it have been prevented through maintenance and dozens of other things . if after i have all the facts i find that someone was at fault for it happening then i can there ass . making assumptions based on no evidence but someones word is the hieght of stupidity from a leadership perspective . refusing to admit you fucked up and apologise to the people that you accused is just being an ass and shows you are a poor leader . <br>
<br>
on my ship i am responsible for the lives of my men , the vessel and the cargo , as well as upholding the laws we operate under and maintaining the company that pays my salaries intrest . if something goes wrong i am the one that answers for it . simc and errtai lead rota , it is there responsibility what happens while they lead . and that will never change .<br>
<br>
<br>
garthin<br>
